mimalloc
------------------------------------------
mimalloc (pronounced 'me-malloc') is a general purpose allocator with excellent
performance characteristics. Initially developed by Daan Leijen for the
run-time systems of the Koka and Lean languages.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.5-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libmimalloc-devel-2.0.9-1bl1
  libmimalloc2-2.0.9-1bl1
  pkg-config-1.9.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.39-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.36.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/microsoft/mimalloc

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/microsoft/mimalloc/archive/refs/tags/v2.0.9.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack mimalloc-2.0.9-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./mimalloc-2.0.9-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/mimalloc-2.0.9-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/mimalloc-2.0.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmimalloc2-2.0.9-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmimalloc-devel-2.0.9-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(mimalloc)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/mimalloc.README
  /usr/share/doc/mimalloc/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/mimalloc/README.md

(libmimalloc2)
  /usr/bin/cygmimalloc-2.dll

(libmimalloc-devel)
  /usr/include/mimalloc-new-delete.h
  /usr/include/mimalloc-override.h
  /usr/include/mimalloc.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/mimalloc/mimalloc-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/mimalloc/mimalloc-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/mimalloc/mimalloc-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/mimalloc/mimalloc.cmake
  /usr/lib/libmimalloc.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/mimalloc.pc

